This is the first record of
Sisyra panama
and the family Sisyridae from Caatinga biome in Brazil . The specimens of
S. panama
were collected in two highland areas, Serra de Ibiapaba, Ubajara ( Ceará state ) and Caeté-Açú, Palmeiras ( Bahia state ), where orographic rainfall is common, thus enabling the existence of wet forest islands surrounded by Caatinga vegetation (
Queiroz et al. 2017
). Serra de Ibiapaba is characterized as a “Brejo de Altitude”, and it is floristically similar to the Amazonia biome (
Takiya et al. 2016
;
Queiroz et al. 2017
). Caeté-Açú is a district of Palmeiras city, located in the Chapada Diamantina Complex, which has phytophysiognomies similar to the Atlantic rainforest and it contains the only Rupestrian Grassland vegetation of the Caatinga (
Queiroz et al. 2017
).
